# RHEV driver for Cirrus
# jlabocki@redhat.com

1. Deployment
	1.1 Edit conf/rhev.conf appropriately for your environment
	1.2 Copy the contents of rhevm/ to the RHEVM scripting library directory on the RHEVM server
	1.3 Add any template maps to conf/templatemap, if you don't want to use a template for any services
		then simple put servicename;none in the templatemap file where servicename is the name of a
		service defined in the CirrusVmList file. (See Cirrus README)


	
